<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="55" type="material examined">
<paragraph pageId="26" pageNumber="55">Material examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="26" pageNumber="55">Holotype. Sumatra, Sungei Kumbang, Korinchi, 4500 ft, Apr. 1914 (BMNH). Other material examined. Male (LMBC, UPOL 001378), Sumatra, Jambi Kersik Tua, Gn. Kerinci, 19.-22. Jan. 2005, 1600-2200 m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="26" pageNumber="55">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="26" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicName authority="Pic, 1921" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Platerodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platerodrilus robinsoni" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robinsoni">Platerodrilus robinsoni</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Pic, 1921" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Platerodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platerodrilus luteus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteus">Platerodrilus luteus</taxonomicName>
in general appearance, but differs in the shape of the phallobase and phallus (Figs 62-63, 67-68).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="55" type="redescription">
<paragraph pageId="26" pageNumber="55">Redescription.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="26" pageNumber="55">Body black; head and mesoscutellum dark brown, pronotum and elytra orange yellow; antennae, and legs dark brown to black (Fig. 6). Head small, antennal tubercles separated by deep groove. Eyes hemispherically prominent, frontal interocular distance 2.1 times maximum eye diameter. Antennae slender, compressed, densely pubescent, antennomere 3 1.1 times longer than antennomere 2. Pronotum transverse, 1.6 times wider than long, anterior margin rounded, frontal angles obtuse, lateral margins slightly convex, posterior angles approximately rectangular (Fig. 19). Elytra parallel-sided, elytra 3.3 times longer than width at humeri, elytral costae weak, covered with dense pubescence. Male genitalia with curved phallus; parameres short, rounded, with slender membranous process; phallobase wide, deeply emarginate (Figs 62-63).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="55" type="measurements">
<paragraph pageId="26" pageNumber="55">Measurements.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="26" pageNumber="55">BL 7.8 mm, PL 1.0 mm, PW 1.6 mm, HW 2.0 mm, Edist 0.85 mm, Ediam 0.40 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="56" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="56">
<pageBreakToken pageId="27" pageNumber="56" start="start">Distribution</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="56">Indonesia: Sumatra.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="56" type="remark">
<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="56">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicName authority="Pic, 1921" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Platerodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platerodrilus robinsoni" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robinsoni">Platerodrilus robinsoni</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Pic, 1921" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Platerodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platerodrilus korinchianus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="korinchianus">Platerodrilus korinchianus</taxonomicName>
in the colouration; but both species are syntopic. Therefore, the species rank is proposed for 
<taxonomicName authority="Pic, 1921" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Platerodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platerodrilus robinsoni" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robinsoni">Platerodrilus robinsoni</taxonomicName>
stat. n.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
